                        <summary><!--SUMMARY--></summary>
                        <textLang mainLang="chg">Chaghatay</textLang>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item1" n="1">
                            <locus from="1a" to="1b">folio 1a-b</locus>
                            <author key="person_f407">anonymous</author>
                            <title key="" type="desc">fragmentary moral and religious exhortations
                                in Chaghatay</title>
                            <incipit>(<locus from="1a" to="1a">folio 1a</locus>) هو یداس (؟) فقیرلیق
                                قیلالوغ لوق قیلمفغیل [...]</incipit>
                            <note>The top of <locus from="1a" to="1a">folio 1a</locus> bears the
                                title هو یداس (؟) فقیرلیق, wherein the first word(s) are not
                                legible. They are, however, repeated in the first line of the text
                                itself. The text(s) is/are written in three or four separate hands,
                                some of which may belong to the same scribe writing at different
                                times. It is unclear if all these texts belong with the same title,
                                or if they are of different origins. Some fragments on the back
                                appear to have been intentionally erased, both with water and by
                                being stricken out.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="chg">Chaghatay</textLang>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item2" n="2">
                            <locus from="2a" to="2b">folio 2a-b</locus>
                            <author key="person_f407">anonymous</author>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x-lc">Ṭarīqa-yi ḫatma-yi Ġaws̠
                                al-a‘ẓām</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg">طریقهٔ ختیمهٔ غوث الاعظم</title>
                            <incipit>(<locus from="2a" to="2a">folio 2a, line 2</locus>) یوز اون بر
                                مرتبه دورود یوز اون بر مرتبه کلمی تمجید [...]</incipit>
                            <explicit>(<locus from="2b" to="2b">folio 2b, right margin</locus>)
                                [...] عجیب فراغتی بار دوستلاریم فقیرلیق‌ننک بلاد محنتی بار اصله
                                پادشاه‌لیق‌ننک</explicit>
                            <note>Notes of unknown origin on the following work.</note>
                            <note>The second word of the title on the top of this page is written
                                ختٮمهٔ. The closest possible reading is ختیمهٔ, though admittedly no
                                likely reading seems to make very good sense in context.</note>
                            <note>There are two hands in this section, the second <locus from="2a"
                                    to="2b">beginning at the bottom of folio 2a and continuing onto
                                    the right margin of folio 2b</locus>. It is unclear if both of
                                these belong to the same title.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="chg">Chaghatay</textLang>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item3" n="3">
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus from="2b" to="127b">folios 2b-127b and</locus>
                                <locus from="129b" to="129b">129b (title only)</locus>
                            </locusGrp>
                            <author key="">
                                <persName xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Mullā ‘Abdu l-rasūl
                                    Kāšġarī</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="chg">ملا عبد الرسول کاشغری</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Manqabatu Ġaws̠ al-s̠aqalayn</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg">منقبة غوث الثقلین</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Kitāb-i ḥażrat-i Ġaws̠
                                al-a‘ẓām</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg">کتاب حضرت غوث الاعظم</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Muḫtaṣar manāqib-i ‘Abdu l-qādir
                                Jīlānī</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg">مختصر مناقب عبد القادر جیلانی</title>
                            <!--<title key="work_9326" xml:lang="per-Latn-x">Tuḥfat al-qādirīyah</title>
                            <title key="work_9326" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Tuḥfatu l-qādirīyya</title>
                            <title key="work_9326" xml:lang="per">تهفة القادریة</title>-->
                            <incipit>(<locus from="2b" to="2b">folio 2b, lines 1-2</locus>) بسم الله
                                الرحمن الرحیم والحمد الله الّذي نوّر قلوب العارفین بنور جمال ذاته
                                [...]</incipit>
                            <explicit>(<locus from="127b" to="127b">folio 127b, lines 11-12</locus>)
                                قیلسا سوز تطویل که انجام تپادورغنی اوجون اجمالا ذکر قیلیندي اوّلا و
                                اخرا بر حمتکه یا ارحم الرحمین</explicit>
                            <colophon>(<locus from="127b" to="127b">folio 127b, line 13</locus>) تمت
                                تمام شد تأریخقه مینک ایکی یوز اللک سکز توشقان یلی</colophon>
                            <note>The virtues (<foreign xml:lang="ara">مناقب</foreign>
                                <foreign xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">manāqib</foreign>) of <persName
                                    role="subject" key="person_71359982"><persName xml:lang="ara"
                                        >سید عبدالقادر الجیلانی</persName>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Sayyid ‘Abd al-Qādir
                                        al-Jīlānī</persName></persName>, a sufi saint. Versions
                                exist in both Arabic and Persian under the title <title
                                    key="work_9326" xml:lang="per">تهفة القادریة</title>, the most
                                popular of which being a Persian version by <persName
                                    key="person_f283"><persName xml:lang="ara">ابو المعالي
                                        محمد</persName>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Abū l-Ma‘ālī
                                        Muḥammad</persName></persName>. Götz (1979: 504, Nr. 534)
                                suggests in his analysis of another manuscript og the same Chagahaty
                                text that this Persian version is only the main source of a number
                                of sources which the author has drawn upon for this Chaghatay work.
                                The name of the author does not appear in this manuscript, but in
                                the manuscript described by Götz (see below).</note>
                            <note>The title of this work can be found again beneath some unrelated
                                notes on folio 129b, repeated over and over in whole or in part
                                seven or so times as <title key="" xml:lang="chg">حضرت سید عبد
                                    القادر جیلانی رضی الله تعالی‌نینک منقبت‌لاری</title>
                                <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Ḥażrat-i ‘Abdu l-qādir Jīlānī
                                    rażī Allāhu ta‘ālānïng manqabatlarï</title>.</note>
                            <note>Kut (2003: 79 § 114) labels this text "MS Ind. Inst. Turk. 14/1,
                                counting only the larger works within this manuscript.</note>
                            <filiation>Another manuscript of the same text appears in <ref
                                    target="https://digital.staatsbibliothek-berlin.de/werkansicht/?PPN=PPN1775158535"
                                    >Staatsbibliothek Berlin Ms. or. oct. 1684</ref>, where it is
                                titled <title key="" xml:lang="chg">مختصر مناقب عبد القادر
                                    جیلانی</title>
                                <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Muḫtaṣar manāqib-i ‘Abdu l-qādir
                                    Jīlānī</title>.</filiation>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                                <bibl><ref
                                        target="https://rep.adw-goe.de/handle/11858/00-001S-0000-0023-9B22-F"
                                        >Götz, Manfred. <title>Verzeichnis der Orientalischen
                                            Handschriften in Deutschland, Band XIII, Teil 4:
                                            Türkische Handschriften</title>. Wiesbaden: Franz
                                        Steiner Verlag Gmbh. 1979.</ref> p. 504, Nr. 534.</bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="chg">Chaghatay</textLang>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item4" n="4">
                            <locus from="128a" to="129a">folios 128a-129a</locus>
                            <author key="person_f407">anonymous</author>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x-lc">Asnād-i munājāt</title>
                            <title key="" xml:lang="chg">اسناد مناجات</title>
                            <incipit>(<locus from="128a" to="128a">folio 128a, lines 1-2</locus>)
                                اسناد مناجات آنحضرت صلی الله علیه و سلم اینست و مکرم عفو إلآفات
                                عظیم البرکات و عموم الدعوات اینست [...]</incipit>
                            <explicit>(<locus from="129a" to="129a">folio 129a, lines 12-13</locus>)
                                [...] و سه بار کلمهٔ شهادت بخوانی چنان بود که چو درا از آتش دوزخ
                                آزاد کرده باشی</explicit>
                            <note>A lengthy passage of littanies (مناجات munājāt) in supplication to
                                various sufi saints, written in heavily formulaic Persian. The
                                origin of these littanies is unknown, and they do not appear to be
                                from any of the more famous Persian مناجات‌نامه munājātnamah.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item5" n="5">
                            <locusGrp>
                                <locus from="129b" to="129b">folios 129b and</locus>
                                <locus from="188b" to="188b">188b</locus>
                            </locusGrp>
                            <author key="person_f407">anonymous</author>
                            <title key="">a Chaghatay record of the deaths of various sufis</title>
                            <incipit>(<locus from="129b" to="129b">folio 129b, first line of
                                    unobscured text</locus>) [...] تاءریخ‌قه بر مینک ایکی یوز آتمش
                                بش ااط (= آط ؟) یلی سفر آینینک اون سکزی دوشنبه کونی سرلارکا </incipit>
                            <explicit>(<locus from="188b" to="188b">folio 188b, line 7</locus>) رحلت
                                قیلغان [...]</explicit>
                            <note>Two separate pages of records (some incomplete) of the death dates
                                of individuals who appear, by the names and the contexts of the
                                manuscript, to be members of the same sufi circles to which the
                                anonymous author(s) belonged. It is unclear how the two pages relate
                                to one another besides being similar in form and content, or why
                                they should be so far apart in the manuscript. Several of the
                                records on <locus from="129b" to="129b">folio 129b</locus> have also
                                been erased or stricken through.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="chg">Chaghatay</textLang>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item6" n="6">
                            <locus from="130a" to="130a">folio 130a</locus>
                            <author key="person_100648969" role="att">
                                <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Ja‘far al-Ṣādiq</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ara">جعفر الصادق</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title key="" type="desc">excerpt from a commentary on the companions of
                                the cave</title>
                            <incipit>(<locus from="130a" to="130a">folio 130a, line 1-3</locus>) بسم
                                الله الرحمن الرحیم اللهم انی اسٸلك باسلام یملیخا ورغبته وبایمان
                                مکسلمینا ومعرفته [...]</incipit>
                            <note>A single page of with a variant of an Arabic commentary on the
                                Companions of the Cave (اصحاب الکهف Aṣḥāb al-Kahf, a.k.a. the Seven
                                Sleepers) attributed to <persName key="person_100648969">
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara">جعفر الصادق</persName>
                                    <persName xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc">Ja‘far al-Ṣādiq</persName>
                                </persName>, which invokes the virtues of the sleepers. The names of
                                the sleepers differs slightly here than in most versions of the
                                text.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="ara">Arabic</textLang>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Ind_Inst_Turk_14-item7" n="7">
                            <locus from="130b" to="181b">folios 130b-181b</locus>
                            <author key="person_98317185" role="att">
                                <persName>I︠A︡savi, Akhmed, d. 1166</persName> = <persName
                                    xml:lang="chg">خواجه احمد یسوی</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Ḫwāja Aḥmad Yasawī</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title key="work_1945" xml:lang="chg">حکمت حضرت سلطان خواجه</title>
                            <title key="work_1945" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Ḥikmat-i ḥażrat-i Sulṭān
                                Ḫwāja</title>
                            <title key="work_1945" xml:lang="chg">دیوان حکمت</title>
                            <title key="work_1945" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Dīwān-i Ḥikmat</title>
                            <title key="work_1945" xml:lang="chg-Latn-x">Dēwān-i Ḥikmat</title>
                            <incipit>(<locus from="130b" to="130b">folio 130b, headpiece + line
                                    1</locus>) [...] بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم حق تعالی فضل برله فرمان
                                یتی </incipit>
                            <note>49 ḥikmats from the divan traditionally attributed to Aḥmad
                                Yasawī, though almost certainly dating to a period several centuries
                                later than his death.</note>
                            <note>Kut (2003: 104 § 152) labels this text "MS Ind. Inst. Turk. 14/2,
                                counting only the larger works within this manuscript.</note>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Kut, Günay. <title>Supplementary catalogue of Turkish
                                        manuscripts in the Bodleian Library with reprint of the 1930
                                        catalogue by H. Ethé</title>. Oxford: Oxford University
                                    Press. 2003. p. 79 § 114. </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="chg">Chaghatay</textLang>
                        </msItem>

